		<td><b>Plotting pixels [?]</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />- No clues about the exact hardware procedure, though my emu runs 1 cycle of PPU, generates 1 background pixel (4 bits), it's ORed with color emphasis if required and transfered into a surface (bitmap). Once it's there, it can't be changed, since the palette is already loaded.
<br />
<br />- My question is... Let's assume it's correct. If I change the palette, it's possible to plot another pixel using another color. In other words, it's possible to display all the possible NES colors in a single frame...?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
